'''Sonja Tallis''' (born 24 September 1943) is an Australian actress, singer and drama teacher.
==Performance career==
Tallis began her showbiz career as a folk singer, touring as part of a duo called "Sean & Sonja", before moving onto acting. After acting in serial ''[[The Young Doctors]]'', she had a small role in ''[[Sons and Daughters (Australian TV series)|Sons and Daughters]]'', before going onto her best-known role, as top dog, Nora Flynn, in ''[[Prisoner (TV series)|Prisoner]]'' which she played for six months between May and November 1985.<ref name="Zuk 2">{{cite web | url = http://www.australiantelevision.net/prisoner.html | title = ''Prisoner (Cell Block H)'' | last = Zuk | first = Tony | date = 30 December 1998 | work = Australian Television Information Archive | accessdate = 21 June 2017 | deadurl = bot: unknown | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/21124/20060307-0000/www.australiantelevision.net/prisoner.html | archivedate = 7 March 2006 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> She went on to a regular role in the short-lived Crawford's series ''[[Prime Time (Australian TV series)|Prime Time]]'', as Georgina Jones, in 1986.<ref name="Zuk 1">{{cite web | url = http://www.australiantelevision.net/primetime.html | title = Australian Television: ''Prime Time'' | last = Zuk | first = Tony | date = 26 August 2005 | work = Australian Television Information Archive | accessdate = 21 June 2017 | deadurl = bot: unknown | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/21124/20121122-1616/www.australiantelevision.net/primetime.html | archivedate = 22 November 2012 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> She appeared in ''[[Home and Away]]'' and ''[[McLeod's Daughters]]''.
== Teaching ==
Tallis has taught drama, both privately and in a number of schools in Sydney.
